WEBVTT

00:03.104 --> 00:04.738
*

00:11.112 --> 00:12.580
(iPhone unlock sound)

00:12.613 --> 00:15.049
(iPhone lock sound,
puts phone down)

00:17.751 --> 00:19.553
* You were right

00:19.587 --> 00:20.854
(whispers):
Jimmy.

00:22.556 --> 00:23.691
Hey, buddy.

00:23.724 --> 00:25.726
You okay?

00:27.395 --> 00:28.662
Good morning.

00:28.696 --> 00:29.830
About what?

00:29.863 --> 00:33.567
God! Absolutely
blotto last night.

00:33.601 --> 00:35.069
(chuckles)

00:35.103 --> 00:37.405
You... You don't remember
what I told you?

00:37.438 --> 00:38.439
No.

00:38.472 --> 00:41.041
But tell me again.

00:41.075 --> 00:42.510
Okay, seriously, dude.

00:42.543 --> 00:44.445
I think you might have
a drinking problem.

00:44.478 --> 00:46.747
Like, you need to go
to church basements and shit.

00:46.780 --> 00:49.383
Oh, my God.
Okay, um...

00:49.417 --> 00:51.619
(inhales)

00:51.652 --> 00:55.323
I am... so sorry,
but, uh...

00:57.825 --> 00:59.960
Sweetheart,
your dad died.

01:02.796 --> 01:04.798
What?

01:04.832 --> 01:06.100
Papa?

01:06.134 --> 01:07.601
Oh, my God.

01:07.635 --> 01:09.903
I know. Oh, God. I'm so sorry.

01:09.937 --> 01:13.574
I... I don't know what to say.

01:25.453 --> 01:27.455
*

01:39.133 --> 01:40.768
(exhales)

01:40.801 --> 01:42.836
Do you want to talk about it?

01:45.439 --> 01:46.740
Ha!

01:46.774 --> 01:48.676
I was kidding.
I totally remembered.

01:48.709 --> 01:50.110
Wait... what?

01:50.144 --> 01:51.145
You knew?

01:51.179 --> 01:52.646
Yeah. You told me last night.

01:52.680 --> 01:53.981
You're not getting
that one back.

01:54.014 --> 01:56.484
I stole one, dummy.
Jimmy!

01:56.517 --> 01:59.687
You do not need
to steal blow jobs.
Yeah, but

01:59.720 --> 02:01.789
you know how amazing
free food tastes.

02:01.822 --> 02:03.691
(urinating)

02:03.724 --> 02:05.293
(toilet flushes)
Seriously, are you okay?

02:05.326 --> 02:07.195
Your dad died.
That's a big deal.

02:07.228 --> 02:09.630
Yes, I am absolutely fine.

02:09.663 --> 02:11.499
I feel... nothing about it.

02:11.532 --> 02:13.301
Really?
Yeah.

02:13.334 --> 02:15.636
Great!

02:15.669 --> 02:18.005
Oh. Phew! Thank
God that's over.

02:18.038 --> 02:21.475
Huh? Hey, do you want to do, uh,
one of those Korean gel masks?

02:21.509 --> 02:24.645
Not really.
I got a snail one.

02:24.678 --> 02:27.448
It's supposed to be extra goopy.

02:27.481 --> 02:29.149
Huh.

02:34.154 --> 02:36.957
* I'm gonna leave you anyway

02:36.990 --> 02:39.693
* I'm gonna leave you
anyway *

02:39.727 --> 02:43.030
* Gonna leave you anyway.

02:50.571 --> 02:54.875
I made my special
heart pancakes,

02:54.908 --> 02:56.744
because we love you, Jimmy.

02:56.777 --> 03:00.013
We really do.
What kind of
jank-ass hearts are these?

03:00.047 --> 03:01.549
That one looks like a butt.

03:01.582 --> 03:03.551
Sorry. It was...
it was kind of a rough night.

03:03.584 --> 03:05.653
Uh, but later this afternoon,
I'm finally gonna have

03:05.686 --> 03:07.921
my consultation with
the chief of staff at the VA.

03:07.955 --> 03:09.990
Yeah, chiefs'll do that
sometimes.

03:10.023 --> 03:13.160
Hey, can I get some sticky sauce
for these pan-butts or what?

03:13.193 --> 03:14.562
Do you know,
I actually just

03:14.595 --> 03:16.997
read something
interesting about PTSD?

03:17.030 --> 03:19.600
Oh, yeah?
Yeah, it turns out
in World War I,

03:19.633 --> 03:22.236
the official term for
"PTSD" was "cowardice,"

03:22.270 --> 03:24.505
and you were
shot for it.
That is interesting.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.039
LINDSAY:
How are you holding up, Jimmy?

03:26.073 --> 03:27.741
My guinea pig died.

03:27.775 --> 03:30.244
I couldn't jack off
for, like, half a day.

03:30.278 --> 03:31.779
I'm telling you
guys-- false alarm.

03:31.812 --> 03:33.247
He truly doesn't
give a shit.

03:33.281 --> 03:35.182
Look, when a relationship

03:35.215 --> 03:38.852
has been virtually non-existent
for 33 years,

03:38.886 --> 03:41.255
we're not talking
about a major tectonic shift.

03:41.289 --> 03:43.056
Nothing has changed.

03:43.090 --> 03:45.759
I still have exactly
zero off-track bettors

03:45.793 --> 03:47.595
with IBS in my daily life.

03:47.628 --> 03:49.530
I almost wish I knew
more dead people.

03:49.563 --> 03:52.266
I think funerals are hella sexy.

03:52.300 --> 03:54.302
All right, everybody out.
I have work to do.

03:54.335 --> 03:56.136
Wait!

03:56.169 --> 03:59.206
Jimmy's dad died,
and he doesn't care.

03:59.239 --> 04:02.310
Yes?
I'm going to have a baby.

04:02.343 --> 04:04.211
JIMMY:
What's happening?
Is Lindsay

04:04.244 --> 04:06.046
processing thought?

04:06.079 --> 04:08.616
Shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh.
And when I'm old,

04:08.649 --> 04:13.554
my kid will have a feeling
about me dying.

04:13.587 --> 04:14.888
(whispering):
Oh, my God, she's doing it.

04:14.922 --> 04:17.458
I want my kids to be sad
when I die.

04:17.491 --> 04:20.060
Yes?
So I need to be

04:20.093 --> 04:22.229
a good... a good...

04:22.262 --> 04:24.031
This is really happening.
a good...

04:25.198 --> 04:26.567
(sighs)

04:26.600 --> 04:27.835
...dad.

04:27.868 --> 04:30.504
Aah! It almost had it.
Oh.

04:30.538 --> 04:33.106
I should probably sign up
for one of those stupid

04:33.140 --> 04:35.075
classes Becca's always
yammering about.

04:35.108 --> 04:36.444
Edgar? Edgar?

04:36.477 --> 04:37.911
Uh, yeah. What's up?

04:37.945 --> 04:39.813
Big writing day ahead
of me. I need you to get

04:39.847 --> 04:42.816
all my usual writing snacks from
the British specialty store.

04:42.850 --> 04:44.652
Shrimp-flavored crisps,

04:44.685 --> 04:46.620
Wallenger's choco-knockers,
tartar biscuits,

04:46.654 --> 04:48.121
and then all your
standard candies--

04:48.155 --> 04:50.290
lemingtons, fluffingtons,
rum Christophers,

04:50.324 --> 04:51.959
salted licorice knib knobs.

04:51.992 --> 04:53.527
I'm not mad, Felix.

04:53.561 --> 04:55.763
No, and when you constantly
accuse me of being mad,

04:55.796 --> 04:58.466
you deny my right of actually
being goddamn mad at you.

04:58.499 --> 05:00.868
No, I'm not "therapizing" you,
all right?

05:00.901 --> 05:02.269
Stop saying that.

05:02.302 --> 05:04.304
Holy shit.

05:04.338 --> 05:05.839
I-I'll call you later.

05:05.873 --> 05:08.476
What's up? Give me a cigarette.
Who was that?

05:08.509 --> 05:10.644
What that your shitty boyfriend
with his cargo shorts?

05:10.678 --> 05:12.045
None of your business.

05:12.079 --> 05:14.214
(grunts)

05:14.247 --> 05:16.316
What's going on?

05:16.350 --> 05:20.521
So, I told Jimmy his dad died,
like you told me to, and he said

05:20.554 --> 05:23.023
that he feels nothing,
and then he stole a beej,

05:23.056 --> 05:25.325
which is a pretty good
heckle, actually.

05:25.359 --> 05:26.960
Is there a question?
Nope.

05:26.994 --> 05:30.297
I just wanted you to know
that you were wrong.

05:30.330 --> 05:33.000
You were wrong.

05:33.033 --> 05:35.302
Jimmy can say he's
fine all he wants,

05:35.335 --> 05:38.038
but sooner or later, his
dad's death is gonna hit him,

05:38.071 --> 05:41.041
and when it does, you're gonna
have to be there for him.

05:41.074 --> 05:44.077
When? We're going
on a rad cruise.

05:44.111 --> 05:46.980
Are you saying this could
come out on the rad cruise?

05:47.014 --> 05:49.349
Sure. Yes, it could
happen on the rad cruise.

05:49.383 --> 05:51.852
(clears throat)
What's the rad cruise?

05:51.885 --> 05:54.555
No, I don't want to know.
I mean, I do want to...

05:54.588 --> 05:57.691
Never mind.
So you're telling me

05:57.725 --> 06:00.728
I need to help him
get it all out now,

06:00.761 --> 06:02.896
just pop it like a pimple.

06:02.930 --> 06:05.365
No, that is not how humans work.
Yeah, I get it.

06:05.399 --> 06:08.368
Get him to cry, boo-hoo, there,
there, we'll be done by Wheel.

06:09.803 --> 06:12.272
Of Fortune.
Seven years in school? Really?

06:12.305 --> 06:15.843
Gretchen, Jimmy has got to go
through his grieving process.

06:15.876 --> 06:17.377
All right?

06:17.411 --> 06:19.580
It's not gonna happen
on your exact schedule.

06:19.613 --> 06:22.049
Eh. I think
I'm gonna do it my way.

06:22.082 --> 06:23.684
Thanks for nothing.

06:23.717 --> 06:25.118
(clears throat)

06:25.152 --> 06:27.220
(whispers):
Your boyfriend... sucks.

06:27.254 --> 06:29.623
Sucks.

06:31.625 --> 06:35.062
Simon's sisters and Kitty
sprawled on the carpet,

06:35.095 --> 06:38.198
watching Top of the Pops,
their bums in the air.

06:38.231 --> 06:40.968
From his perch on the coach,
Simon noted

06:41.001 --> 06:44.371
that while Cynthia and Patsy
had gotten quite porcine,

06:44.404 --> 06:47.641
Kitty's bottom had
an almost otherworldly lift,

06:47.675 --> 06:50.578
as if in the process
of being raptured

06:50.611 --> 06:54.147
for being too perfect to dwell
any longer on Earth.

06:54.181 --> 06:56.650
(yells in frustration)

06:56.684 --> 06:58.919
Goddamn it!

06:58.952 --> 07:00.488
What's wrong with me?

07:00.521 --> 07:02.289
It's been hours,

07:02.322 --> 07:04.492
and I still haven't perfected
the bum metaphor.

07:04.525 --> 07:06.727
My fingers hurt.
My dad died.

07:06.760 --> 07:09.763
At least you know where he is.
Edgar, I need sustenance.
Where are my snacks?

07:09.797 --> 07:12.566
Uh, sorry, Jimmy. There was some
police activity near the store.

07:12.600 --> 07:14.502
That's my last food!

07:14.535 --> 07:16.136
I've been thinking
about it all day,

07:16.169 --> 07:18.906
and you really need to cry,
Jimmy. My therapist says

07:18.939 --> 07:20.941
it's very...
Gretchen the sheer breadth

07:20.974 --> 07:24.444
of my labyrinthian abstruse
psychological composition

07:24.478 --> 07:26.780
cannot possibly be
second-handedly grasped

07:26.814 --> 07:30.183
by some Long Beach
Community College graduate

07:30.217 --> 07:32.920
who deals with the...
tragically maladroit all day.

07:32.953 --> 07:34.321
No offense.

07:34.354 --> 07:36.790
None taken,
because I do not know that word.

07:36.824 --> 07:38.425
Just give me
the afternoon.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.160
We'll do some super-sad shit,

07:40.193 --> 07:42.630
you'll poop out some tears
and we'll be home by Wheel.

07:42.663 --> 07:45.165
BOTH:
...of Fortune.

07:49.503 --> 07:51.672
It won't work. I feel nothing!

07:51.705 --> 07:54.608
But fine. Let's go.

07:54.642 --> 07:56.376
Work day's already a disaster.

07:56.409 --> 07:58.111
I don't know why
I'm suddenly blocked.

07:58.145 --> 08:01.014
I'm rewriting the same paragraph
over and over.

08:01.048 --> 08:02.349
Hey,

08:02.382 --> 08:04.151
Killswitch, while I'm out,

08:04.184 --> 08:06.353
copy edit the chapter where
Simon watches Kitty bathe

08:06.386 --> 08:07.721
after the trip-hop concert.

08:07.755 --> 08:09.356
Oh, and for the love of God,

08:09.389 --> 08:12.259
finally learn how to spell
"analingus," will you?!

08:13.493 --> 08:15.529
You never say "thank you."

08:15.563 --> 08:18.699
That's what the money's for!

08:32.212 --> 08:35.182
I'm so glad we're gonna
learn how to be a family.

08:35.215 --> 08:36.483
Family.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.151
But we're already a family.

08:38.185 --> 08:41.321
You can't just have two
people in a family, Paul.

08:41.354 --> 08:43.490
Name one family
that's two people.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.392
Gilmore Girls.

08:45.425 --> 08:47.394
We have to learn how
to be good parents,

08:47.427 --> 08:51.064
so that when we're old,
they'll take good care of us.

08:51.098 --> 08:53.366
Plus, you're so
accident-prone.

08:53.400 --> 08:55.703
You turned into my knife,
and it's taken, like,

08:55.736 --> 08:58.038
forever for your skin
to grow back together.

08:58.071 --> 08:59.206
You mean heal?

08:59.239 --> 09:01.208
Dogs heel, Paul.

09:01.241 --> 09:02.976
Men get strong.

09:04.277 --> 09:05.913
Nerds!
Oh, my God.

09:05.946 --> 09:08.181
I still can't believe
you're keeping it.

09:08.215 --> 09:10.250
(laughing):
Oh, Rebecca,

09:10.283 --> 09:12.753
you josher.
(laughing)
(chuckling)

09:12.786 --> 09:15.623
Such a bummer
about the timing though.

09:15.656 --> 09:17.357
By the time
it comes flopping out,

09:17.390 --> 09:19.426
our entire family's
gonna be so babied out,

09:19.459 --> 09:22.529
your poor little lump's
not gonna get any attention.

09:22.562 --> 09:25.465
You're just mad
I didn't get all fat like you.

09:25.498 --> 09:27.534
