13:33.146 --> 13:34.547
Thank you.

13:34.581 --> 13:37.350
Okay, we got a little
distracted at that last place.

13:37.384 --> 13:40.053
But this is it:
living fathers

13:40.087 --> 13:42.022
with their kids.
That is some straight-up

13:42.055 --> 13:44.524
"Cat's in the Cradle" shit
right there. Plus,

13:44.557 --> 13:46.393
look at my dope maze.

13:46.426 --> 13:49.229
Usually, I'm a master
of all art forms--

13:49.262 --> 13:51.231
writing, music, quips,

13:51.264 --> 13:52.900
mixed media collage--

13:52.933 --> 13:56.203
but, for some reason,
I am creatively blocked.

13:56.236 --> 13:59.272
A sun wearing sunglasses.

14:01.208 --> 14:02.509
Doesn't even make sense.

14:02.542 --> 14:04.744
He's too bright
for his own eyes?

14:04.777 --> 14:07.080
It's because you need
to cry it out.

14:07.114 --> 14:09.082
Maybe you're right.

14:09.116 --> 14:10.750
MAN:
Jesus Christ.

14:10.783 --> 14:13.921
I don't even know what
to do with you anymore!

14:15.422 --> 14:17.324
And... jackpot.

14:17.357 --> 14:18.758
Go. Follow him.

14:18.791 --> 14:20.593
Maybe he'll rage-kick
a garbage can,

14:20.627 --> 14:22.062
remind you of your dad. Go.

14:22.095 --> 14:23.830
All right.
(clears throat)

14:23.863 --> 14:26.099
I will give it a go.

14:28.401 --> 14:29.569
(bell jingles)

14:29.602 --> 14:32.605
Hey. What you
workin' on, buddy?

14:36.609 --> 14:38.578
Parenting, right?

14:38.611 --> 14:40.080
I don't know
what to do, man.

14:40.113 --> 14:41.448
Mm.

14:41.481 --> 14:44.417
It's hard to communicate
with them, yeah?

14:44.451 --> 14:46.519
Like you don't even recognize
yourself in them.

14:46.553 --> 14:47.620
I don't.

14:47.654 --> 14:48.888
You're frustrated

14:48.922 --> 14:50.890
because he's a little clumsy,

14:50.924 --> 14:53.560
a little too artsy-fartsy,

14:53.593 --> 14:57.064
because he broke a blood vessel
in his eye crying at My Girl.

14:57.097 --> 14:59.066
What? No.

14:59.099 --> 15:01.134
He's legitimately a bad person.

15:01.168 --> 15:03.303
Like, my son
is an awful human being.

15:03.336 --> 15:07.074
What?
He set up a bunch of Facebook
accounts to cyberbully me.

15:07.107 --> 15:09.909
Hey, this bitch
is bothering me.

15:09.943 --> 15:12.045
You trying to hit
on my dad, twink?

15:12.079 --> 15:14.381
Jimmy, turns out
this kid sucks.

15:14.414 --> 15:16.083
You suck! What
kind of adults go

15:16.116 --> 15:18.285
to a paint-your-own-pottery
place anyway?

15:18.318 --> 15:19.919
Nasty-ass
pedophiles.

15:19.953 --> 15:24.091
(laughs)
Oh, shit!
(chuckles)

15:24.124 --> 15:25.758
Don't go...
Shut up, Greg.

15:25.792 --> 15:27.327
I wish you would call me Dad.

15:27.360 --> 15:29.963
Well, I wish you'd
suck my dick.

15:31.698 --> 15:34.001
Oh, hey,
emotion check.

15:35.602 --> 15:37.804
Actually, I think
I felt something that time.

15:37.837 --> 15:40.073
Really?! Jimmy!

15:40.107 --> 15:42.142
We're thawing
your cold, dead heart.

15:42.175 --> 15:44.911
Hurry up! We got one more stop
on the sadness tour.

15:44.944 --> 15:46.413
Okay. Let me call an Edgar.

15:46.446 --> 15:48.415
(sighs)

15:48.448 --> 15:49.616
(line ringing)

15:49.649 --> 15:51.351
We're ready to go.

15:51.384 --> 15:54.121
And I sincerely hope
you've got our car booze.

15:54.154 --> 15:56.623
Sorry, Jimmy, I can't come.
My car broke down.

15:56.656 --> 15:58.191
Oh, well, that's not a surprise.

15:58.225 --> 16:02.329
Piece of shit with
no auxiliary plug or car booze!

16:12.739 --> 16:13.673
All right.

16:21.248 --> 16:23.650
Great job.
Here's a Sophie giraffe

16:23.683 --> 16:25.852
for winning
the skills section.
(gasps)

16:25.885 --> 16:27.687
(chuckles)

16:27.720 --> 16:29.889
Oh. No, that's...
(squeaking)

16:29.922 --> 16:31.824
Okay.

16:31.858 --> 16:34.027
(gasps)
I won a prize.

16:34.061 --> 16:35.495
You're such a natural mommy.

16:35.528 --> 16:37.964
One of the dads just
told me the neatest thing:

16:37.997 --> 16:39.466
babies are programmed

16:39.499 --> 16:41.568
to look like the father
when they're born.

16:41.601 --> 16:43.170
Won't that be
so adorable?

16:43.203 --> 16:45.505
A tiny little me suckling
at your bosom?

16:45.538 --> 16:48.108
Wah, wah.
(suckling sounds)

16:49.442 --> 16:52.412
Linds...
(clears throat)

16:52.445 --> 16:55.748
that was actually quite...
impressive.

16:55.782 --> 16:59.752
I can't believe I'm actually
saying this, but I think...

16:59.786 --> 17:01.921
you were born to be a mom.

17:01.954 --> 17:03.423
Thanks, Bec.

17:03.456 --> 17:04.524
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.
VERNON:
Uh-oh!

17:04.557 --> 17:05.525
There's something's wrong

17:05.558 --> 17:07.194
with my big ol' honkers!

17:07.227 --> 17:09.762
Ah! No leche!

17:09.796 --> 17:12.832
Glug, glug, glug,
glug, glug.
Oh. This poor dear.

17:12.865 --> 17:14.934
He is so delirious
from working

17:14.967 --> 17:17.504
so many double shifts.
Paul, will you drive us home?
Ooh...

17:17.537 --> 17:20.073
Of course. See
you at home, Mama?

17:20.107 --> 17:21.241
Sure, Pap...

17:21.274 --> 17:23.410
Paul.

17:23.443 --> 17:26.846
Um, hi,
what is this?

17:26.879 --> 17:29.082
What do I look like,
some baby lady?

17:29.116 --> 17:32.952
I'm sorry. M-My wife,
she's stuck at work-- shocker.

17:32.985 --> 17:35.255
She gave me this
shopping list, and,

17:35.288 --> 17:37.724
man, I have no idea
what I'm doing.

17:37.757 --> 17:39.792
Oh. Okay.

17:39.826 --> 17:41.628
Mm.

17:41.661 --> 17:44.063
Looks like you're gonna need
a Miracle Blanket, a Woombie,

17:44.097 --> 17:46.466
a Boppy-- really great
neck support--
Yeah...

17:46.499 --> 17:49.702
and, of course,
Zipadee-Zip.

17:49.736 --> 17:51.771
It'll be quicker
if I just do it.

17:51.804 --> 17:54.241
Thank you so much.
I appreciate it.

17:54.274 --> 17:56.309
JIMMY:
Well, Gretchen, you did it.

17:56.343 --> 17:59.479
I can't think of a place
more gloomy, more soul-crushing,

17:59.512 --> 18:02.715
more quintessentially
England.

18:02.749 --> 18:06.619
(bad British accent):
Yeah, I thought you might want
a wee English breakfast.

18:06.653 --> 18:08.821
Excuse me?
Don't be a berk.

18:08.855 --> 18:12.592
You know what I'm talkin' about,
Shitty Jimmy.

18:12.625 --> 18:14.994
Are you being Ronny?
(American accent):
Today's been all abstract.

18:15.027 --> 18:16.463
It's time to personalize it.

18:16.496 --> 18:18.898
I even boned up
on some British slang online.

18:18.931 --> 18:21.634
(British accent): Blarmy!
Knob jockeys getting married?!

18:21.668 --> 18:24.070
Next thing you know,
some ringburner's

18:24.103 --> 18:26.072
gonna want to shag
and marry his dachshund!

18:26.105 --> 18:27.607
(shuddering):
Oh.

18:27.640 --> 18:29.976
Almost felt something again.
Get more personal.

18:30.009 --> 18:32.412
Uh, talk about my
ceramic pony collection

18:32.445 --> 18:34.414
or the time Fiona caught me
kissing a magazine cover

18:34.447 --> 18:36.516
of Boy George because I thought
he was a girl.

18:36.549 --> 18:38.818
Look at 'at pasty skin.

18:38.851 --> 18:41.821
Them soft girl hands.

18:41.854 --> 18:43.323
The poofy scrote

18:43.356 --> 18:46.326
never worked an honest day
in his whole miserable,

18:46.359 --> 18:47.827
sodding life.

18:47.860 --> 18:51.198
Now, you listen to me,
you fat, grey void.

18:51.231 --> 18:54.201
Writing is hard!
It is actual work.

18:54.234 --> 18:58.104
It's a noble, nay, spiritual
endeavor that taxes

18:58.137 --> 19:00.673
both the brain... Oh, my God.

19:00.707 --> 19:03.510
This wretched idea of yours
might actually be working.

19:03.543 --> 19:06.879
The feeling? It's back.
Yeah, it's coming.

19:06.913 --> 19:09.982
Oh, my God.
Here it comes.

19:10.750 --> 19:14.754
(farting)

19:16.223 --> 19:18.225
That was the feeling? A fart?

19:18.258 --> 19:21.294
Mm. Apparently.
Well, I told you,

19:21.328 --> 19:22.962
I'm very evolved.

19:22.995 --> 19:25.298
Stupid therapist.

19:25.332 --> 19:26.799
I'm warning you,
this better be it.

19:26.833 --> 19:28.301
If you lose your shit
on the cruise

19:28.335 --> 19:30.303
and ruin my time
with Cotton Candy Raccoon,

19:30.337 --> 19:32.305
Bubble Gecko, or Sneezy Panda,

19:32.339 --> 19:36.243
I... Well, she died in
a plane crash. But never mind.

19:38.177 --> 19:40.680
How do you even
mess up toast?

19:40.713 --> 19:41.948
(sputtering)

19:45.184 --> 19:47.153
Thanks so much for helping.

19:47.186 --> 19:50.323
Jesus, I'm already
this overwhelmed.

19:50.357 --> 19:52.559
I don't even
have a baby yet.

19:52.592 --> 19:54.661
How are you this good at it
already?

19:54.694 --> 19:57.330
I have no idea.
(chuckles)

19:57.364 --> 20:00.166
So now what? I'm just stuck
doing this baby shit

20:00.199 --> 20:02.001
for the rest of my life?

20:02.034 --> 20:04.070
What if there are
other things I'm meant to be

20:04.103 --> 20:05.905
and I never find out?

20:05.938 --> 20:09.842
Like a phlebologist
or a dinosaur?
(chuckles)

20:09.876 --> 20:12.245
Once my ex and I split,

20:12.279 --> 20:15.582
I figured that was it.

20:15.615 --> 20:17.584
I was never gonna be a dad.

20:17.617 --> 20:21.454
Then I meet this cute Asian
chick at the Kubrick exhibit

20:21.488 --> 20:24.457
at LACMA and suddenly
she's knocked up

20:24.491 --> 20:29.462
and I get this
second chance at 42.

20:29.496 --> 20:31.564
So you believe
in second chances?

20:31.598 --> 20:33.065
I didn't.

20:33.099 --> 20:35.902
But I guess I do now.

20:37.236 --> 20:39.639
(chuckles)

20:44.143 --> 20:47.647
Oh, Jesus. What the hell are
you doing? Are you insane?

20:47.680 --> 20:50.783
I just told you, I'm
on my second chance!

20:50.817 --> 20:54.421
I just thought...
Oh, my God! What
is wrong with you?!

20:54.454 --> 20:56.923
Why would you even do that?
I talked to your husband!
Shh. Okay.

20:56.956 --> 20:59.258
He was so nice. We're going
kayaking together sometime!
Fine.

20:59.292 --> 21:02.995
Shut up. Shut up. Shut up.
This isn't a singles bar
where you just pick up guys!

21:03.029 --> 21:05.097
You're having a baby,
you weirdo!
Shut up, shut up,

21:05.131 --> 21:05.965
shut up.

21:05.998 --> 21:06.966
Shut up.

21:06.999 --> 21:10.036
(squeaking)
Shut up.

21:12.271 --> 21:15.074
(whimpering)
(squeaks)

21:15.107 --> 21:17.810
(door opens, closes)

21:28.287 --> 21:30.457
(door closes)
(Gretchen gasps)

21:30.490 --> 21:32.058
I got your snacks.

21:33.726 --> 21:35.928
(sighs)
It's too late.

21:35.962 --> 21:38.365
I've already lost an
entire day's writing.

21:38.398 --> 21:40.467
Sorry, literature.

21:43.069 --> 21:45.137
Mmm, rum Christophers.

21:45.171 --> 21:47.574
They're so disgusting.
I can't stop eating them.

21:51.310 --> 21:54.180
Hey, how was your thing today?

21:54.213 --> 21:55.181
Fine.

21:55.214 --> 21:57.684
Do you want to talk about it?

21:57.717 --> 21:58.818
No.

21:58.851 --> 22:01.020
Yes. Two for two.

22:01.053 --> 22:03.423
(rapid footfalls)

22:08.728 --> 22:11.664
(sighs)

22:25.378 --> 22:28.114
(sighs)

22:31.350 --> 22:35.154
Well, Dad, here we are,

22:35.187 --> 22:37.690
the final test.

22:44.296 --> 22:47.299
(inhales deeply)

22:51.137 --> 22:53.540
*

23:02.381 --> 23:04.751
That's it.

23:04.784 --> 23:07.253
Get it out.

23:07.286 --> 23:10.289
Let all the sadness out.

23:10.322 --> 23:13.593
Whoa! I thought
you were crying!
No!

23:13.626 --> 23:16.596
It's amazing. I was smelling
the jacket that Dad left,

23:16.629 --> 23:18.364
and it smells exactly like him--

23:18.397 --> 23:20.132
just cigarettes, ale,

23:20.166 --> 23:22.234
beans, occupational failure.

23:22.268 --> 23:25.772
And in a rush, that feeling that
we'd been searching for all day

23:25.805 --> 23:27.073
just came
flying out.

23:27.106 --> 23:29.341
And, Gretchen,
it wasn't sadness.

23:30.076 --> 23:31.644
It was happiness.

23:32.579 --> 23:33.780
I'm free.

23:33.813 --> 23:36.449
I am finally free!

23:36.483 --> 23:39.285
And I'm finally unstuck
creatively.

23:39.318 --> 23:41.387
I found, all right,
the perfect metaphor

23:41.420 --> 23:43.890
for the heft
of Kitty's adolescent bottom.

23:43.923 --> 23:46.626
I'll tell you later.
It's-it's too sexy.

23:46.659 --> 23:48.628
(exhales)
Do you want to go, uh,

23:48.661 --> 23:51.397
binge-watch that six-part series
on the Susan Smith case?

23:51.430 --> 23:53.733
Yeah. Just a sec.
Now that my parental nightmare

23:53.766 --> 23:57.770
is finally over, I'm gonna get
rid of everything that smacks

23:57.804 --> 23:59.405
of Ronny Overly.

23:59.438 --> 24:01.574
May he rest in relative peace

24:01.608 --> 24:03.409
for someone of his arterial

24:03.442 --> 24:05.878
calcification.

